cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CR

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper primarily focuses on mobile ad-hoc networks and routing protocols, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) - The paper discusses unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) and their communication networks, which is a topic closely related to robotics. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The use of GPS information to aid the routing protocol involves control and management of the system, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes an extension to the Optimized Link-State Routing (OLSR) protocol, which involves the use of predictive algorithms, a topic closely related to artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although not the primary focus of the paper, the topic of secure communication in ad-hoc networks is briefly discussed, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security.
